headline: Nasdaq Crosses US$5b Revenue As AI Growth Meets Valuation Questions
summary: Nasdaq reports annual net revenue above $5b for the first time. Management attributes the milestone to organic growth, wider use of AI tools and new fintech offerings. Nasdaq also secures regulatory approvals that expand its trading capabilities, including in digital assets. For investors watching NasdaqGS:NDAQ, this revenue marker highlights how far the business has moved beyond its roots as a US equities exchange.
